import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x="symbol", y="price", data=data, ax=ax, palette="Set3")
    ax.set_xlabel("Company Symbol")
    ax.set_ylabel("Stock Price")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of stock prices across all companies?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='price', hue='symbol', data=data)
    plt.title('How has the stock price of each company changed over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('symbol').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='symbol', y='price', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.title('What is the average stock price for each company?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Company')
    plt.ylabel('Average Stock Price')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.pivot(index='date', columns='symbol', values='price')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='GOOG', y='IBM', color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between stock prices of different companies?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
